## Problem

Many legacy ERP systems use Firebird as their database. When we need to integrate them with modern applications using PostgreSQL, we must synchronize the data.

## Solution Architecture

Firebird (source) → Sync Service → PostgreSQL (target)

## Connecting to Firebird

I use FirebirdSql.Data.FirebirdClient:

```csharp
var connectionString = new FbConnectionStringBuilder
{
    Database = @"C:\\Data\\database.fdb",
    UserID = "SYSDBA",
    Password = "masterkey",
    ServerType = FbServerType.Embedded,
    Charset = "WIN1250"
}.ToString();

using var connection = new FbConnection(connectionString);
await connection.OpenAsync();
```

## Type Mapping

| Firebird | PostgreSQL |
|----------|------------|
| INTEGER | integer |
| BIGINT | bigint |
| VARCHAR(n) | varchar(n) |
| BLOB SUB_TYPE TEXT | text |
| TIMESTAMP | timestamp |
| DECIMAL(p,s) | numeric(p,s) |

## Synchronization Strategy

### Incremental sync

```csharp
public async Task SyncIncrementalAsync()
{
    var lastSync = await GetLastSyncTimestamp();

    var query = @"
        SELECT * FROM ORDERS 
        WHERE MODIFIED_AT > @lastSync
        ORDER BY MODIFIED_AT";

    using var cmd = new FbCommand(query, _fbConnection);
    cmd.Parameters.AddWithValue("@lastSync", lastSync);

    using var reader = await cmd.ExecuteReaderAsync();
    while (await reader.ReadAsync())
    {
        await UpsertToPostgres(reader);
    }

    await UpdateLastSyncTimestamp(DateTime.UtcNow);
}
```

### Upsert to PostgreSQL

```csharp
private async Task UpsertToPostgres(FbDataReader reader)
{
    var sql = @"
        INSERT INTO orders (id, customer_id, total, created_at)
        VALUES (@id, @customerId, @total, @createdAt)
        ON CONFLICT (id) DO UPDATE SET
            customer_id = EXCLUDED.customer_id,
            total = EXCLUDED.total,
            created_at = EXCLUDED.created_at";

    using var cmd = new NpgsqlCommand(sql, _pgConnection);
    cmd.Parameters.AddWithValue("@id", reader.GetInt32(0));
    cmd.Parameters.AddWithValue("@customerId", reader.GetInt32(1));
    cmd.Parameters.AddWithValue("@total", reader.GetDecimal(2));
    cmd.Parameters.AddWithValue("@createdAt", reader.GetDateTime(3));

    await cmd.ExecuteNonQueryAsync();
}
```

## Windows Service with Topshelf

```csharp
public class SyncService : ServiceControl
{
    private Timer _timer;

    public bool Start(HostControl hostControl)
    {
        _timer = new Timer(async _ => await SyncAsync(), 
            null, TimeSpan.Zero, TimeSpan.FromMinutes(5));
        return true;
    }

    public bool Stop(HostControl hostControl)
    {
        _timer?.Dispose();
        return true;
    }
}
```

## Error Handling

1. **Retry with exponential backoff** - for transient errors
2. **Dead letter queue** - for records that can't be synchronized
3. **Alerting** - email on critical errors
